    org.reactivestreams.Processor<T,T>, org.reactivestreams.Publisher<T>, org.reactivestreams.Subscriber<T>, CoreSubscriber<T>, Disposable, Scannable

    public final class DirectProcessor<T>
extends FluxProcessor<T,T>
    Dispatches onNext, onError and onComplete signals to zero-to-many Subscribers.

    This implementation signals an IllegalStateException if a Subscriber is not ready to receive a value due to not requesting enough.

    The implementation ignores Subscriptions push via onSubscribe.

    A terminated DirectProcessor will emit the terminal signal to late subscribers.

      • onSubscribe

        public void onSubscribe(org.reactivestreams.Subscription s)
        从接口复制的说明: org.reactivestreams.Subscriber
        Invoked after calling Publisher.subscribe(Subscriber).

        No data will start flowing until Subscription.request(long) is invoked.

        It is the responsibility of this Subscriber instance to call Subscription.request(long) whenever more data is wanted.

        The Publisher will send notifications only in response to Subscription.request(long).

        参数:
        s - Subscription that allows requesting data via Subscription.request(long)

      • subscribe

        public void subscribe(CoreSubscriber<? super T> actual)
        从类复制的说明: Flux
        An internal Publisher.subscribe(Subscriber) that will bypass Hooks.onLastOperator(Function) pointcut.

        In addition to behave as expected by Publisher.subscribe(Subscriber) in a controlled manner, it supports direct subscribe-time Context passing.

        指定者:
        subscribe 在类中 Flux<T>
        参数:
        actual - the Subscriber interested into the published sequence
